article.headline: Wichita St. 76, Gardner-Webb 64
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Toure Murry scored 13 of his season-high 19 points in the first half as Wichita State beat Gardner-Webb 76-53 on Friday night. J.T. Durley and Clevin Hannah added 12 points each for the Shockers (4-5), who had mustered just 48 points in a loss to TCU four nights earlier. Gardner-Webb (2-6) was led by 17 points each from Auryn MacMillan and Aaron Linn. Trailing 41-32 at halftime, the Bulldogs began narrowing the gap early in the second period and got as close as 49-43 on a Linn jumper with 14:27 left in the game. But Murry and Durley combined for nine of the games's next nine points, and Wichita State led by at least eight the rest of the way. Wichita State was 10-of-27 from 3-point range for a 37 percent clip. Gardner-Webb hit just two of 17 attempted 3-pointers.
